Cross-contract communication macros:

CALL_OTHER_CONTRACT_FUNCTION(contractStateType, function, input, output)
INVOKE_OTHER_CONTRACT_PROCEDURE(contractStateType, procedure, input, output, invocationReward)

Rules:
- Function -> Function: ALLOWED
- Procedure -> Procedure: ALLOWED
- Procedure -> Function: ALLOWED
- Function -> Procedure: FORBIDDEN (functions cannot modify state)
- Called contract must have LOWER contract index
- Define cross-contract input/output in locals struct
- Your contract pays invocationReward QU if the invoked contract consumes it

Example:
struct crossCall_locals
{
    CROSS::setCrossStateNumber_input crossInput;
    CROSS::setCrossStateNumber_output crossOutput;
};

PUBLIC_PROCEDURE_WITH_LOCALS(crossCall)
{
    locals.crossInput.crossStateNumber = input.value;
    INVOKE_OTHER_CONTRACT_PROCEDURE(CROSS, setCrossStateNumber, locals.crossInput, locals.crossOutput, qpi.invocationReward());
}

Inner-contract calls use CALL(functionOrProcedure, input, output) macro.

