Naming conventions:
- Functions/procedures: camelCase (e.g., getStateNumber, setPrice)
- Constants: ALL_CAPS prefixed with contract name (e.g., MYTEST_FEE = 1000)
- State struct: full uppercase (e.g., MYTEST)
- Asset name: max 7 uppercase A-Z/0-9 (e.g., QX, QTRY, QEARN)

Curly braces always on new line:
if (cond)
{
    // ...
}
else
{
    // ...
}

User-defined types: declared INSIDE contract struct to avoid name conflicts.
Constants: use constexpr (e.g., constexpr sint64 MYTEST_FEE = 1000)
Errors: declare as enum ContractNameError { ERROR_1 = 1, ERROR_2, ... }
SELF: contract id (public key), equivalent to id(CONTRACT_INDEX, 0, 0, 0)
SELF_INDEX: contract index number
String: prohibited. Use custom string implementation (UEFIString pattern).
Initialization: always initialize all state in INITIALIZE() procedure.
State is implicitly zero-initialized but explicit init is best practice.
